    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe current line number highlighting group (`CursorLineNr`) is not applied to a line if a virtual line is placed above it.\r\n\r\nThis problem is also relevant with the `virt_lines_above = true` option.\r\n\r\nUpdate: the problem is observed when setting the line number in `statuscolumn`. If `vim.opt.number=true` is set normally, the highlighting is applied correctly.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/46977173/08c73bd1-a48a-4471-8fcf-8920acff1b58\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nMinimal init.lua:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.number = true\r\nvim.opt.statuscolumn = ' %=%l  '\r\nvim.opt.cursorline = true\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.colorscheme('habamax')\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufEnter', {\r\n  pattern = 'init.lua',\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('bdcln'), 1, 0, {\r\n      virt_lines = {{{ 'ï…‰ The next line number has a wrong highlight if it is the current line: expected orange', 'Comment' }}},\r\n    })\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun with minimal init.lua:\r\n```bash\r\nnvim -u init.lua init.lua\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIt is expected that the highlighting for the current line number will be `CursorLineNr` instead of `LineNr`.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-1162+g877d04d0f-Homebrew\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOs Ventura 13.5.2\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.30.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbrew install neovim --HEAD",
